The paper deals with the problem of Wyner-Ziv coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on the case where the statistics of the channel generating the side-information is unknown, which is a problem in machine learning and multimedia (cs.MM, cs.SI). The paper also discusses rate-distortion functions, which are commonly used in data compression and storage (cs.DS). Finally, the paper touches on the Heegard-Berger problem, which is a classic problem in information theory and machine learning (cs.LG).
